HEADWORD: Unearth
<hw>Un*earth"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Unearthed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Unearthing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>earth</ets>.]</ety> <def>To drive or draw from the
earth; hence, to uncover; to bring out from concealment; to bring to
light; to disclose; <as>as, to <ex>unearth</ex> a secret</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>unearth</qex> the roof of an old tree.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unearthly</ent>⟦br⟧
